{"info": {"author": "pwwang", "author_email": "pwwang@pwwang.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "# pyppl_require\n\nRequirement manager for [PyPPL](https://github.com/pwwang/PyPPL).\n\n## Installation\nIt requires [pyppl_annotate](https://github.com/pwwang/pyppl_annotate).\n```shell\npip install pyppl_require\n```\n\n## Usage\n```shell\n> pyppl require\nDescription:\n  Process requirement manager\n\nUsage:\n  pyppl require <--pipe AUTO> [OPTIONS]\n\nRequired options:\n  -p, --pipe <AUTO>     - The pipeline script.\n\nOptional options:\n  --install <AUTO>      - Install the requirements.\n                          You can specify a directory (default: $HOME/bin) to install the \\\n                          requirements.\n                          Default: None\n  -h, -H, --help        - Show help message and exit.\n```\n\nTo allow your processes to be analyzed, you have to put a section in annotate using `toml` format:\n```python\npXXX.config.annotate = \"\"\"\n@requires:\n  [bedtools]\n  validate: \"bedtools --version\"\n  install: \"conda install -c bioconda bedtools\"\n  # other annotations\n\"\"\"\n```\n\nIf you want define those commands using process properties and aggrs:\n```python\npXXX.config.annotate = \"\"\"\n@requires:\n  [bedtools]\n  validate: \"{{args.bedtools}} --version\"\n  install: \"conda install -c bioconda bedtools\"\n  # other annotations\n\"\"\"\n```\n\nInstall to a specify directory:\n\n```python\npXXX.config.annotate = \"\"\"\n@requires:\n  [bedtools]\n  validate: \"{{args.bedtools}} --version\"\n  install: \"conda install -c bioconda bedtools; ln -s $(which bedtools) {{bindir}}/bedtools\"\n  # other annotations\n\"\"\"\n```\n\n`{{bindir}}` will be the directory passed to the command line.\n```shell\npyppl require --pipe <your pipeline> --install </path/to/bin>\n```\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/pwwang/pyppl_require", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "pyppl-require", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pyppl-require/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pyppl-require/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/pwwang/pyppl_require", "Repository": "https://github.com/pwwang/pyppl_require"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/pyppl-require/0.0.3/", "requires_dist": ["cmdy", "pyppl (>=3.0.0,<4.0.0)", "pyppl_annotate"], "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "summary": "Requirement manager for processes of PyPPL", "version": "0.0.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>pyppl_require</h1>\n<p>Requirement manager for <a href=\"https://github.com/pwwang/PyPPL\" rel=\"nofollow\">PyPPL</a>.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>It requires <a href=\"https://github.com/pwwang/pyppl_annotate\" rel=\"nofollow\">pyppl_annotate</a>.</p>\n<pre>pip install pyppl_require\n</pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre>&gt; pyppl require\nDescription:\n  Process requirement manager\n\nUsage:\n  pyppl require &lt;--pipe AUTO&gt; <span class=\"o\">[</span>OPTIONS<span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\nRequired options:\n  -p, --pipe &lt;AUTO&gt;     - The pipeline script.\n\nOptional options:\n  --install &lt;AUTO&gt;      - Install the requirements.\n                          You can specify a directory <span class=\"o\">(</span>default: <span class=\"nv\">$HOME</span>/bin<span class=\"o\">)</span> to install the <span class=\"se\">\\</span>\n                          requirements.\n                          Default: None\n  -h, -H, --help        - Show <span class=\"nb\">help</span> message and exit.\n</pre>\n<p>To allow your processes to be analyzed, you have to put a section in annotate using <code>toml</code> format:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">pXXX</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">annotate</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">@requires:</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  [bedtools]</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  validate: \"bedtools --version\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  install: \"conda install -c bioconda bedtools\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  # other annotations</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">\"\"\"</span>\n</pre>\n<p>If you want define those commands using process properties and aggrs:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">pXXX</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">annotate</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">@requires:</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  [bedtools]</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  validate: \"{{args.bedtools}} --version\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  install: \"conda install -c bioconda bedtools\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  # other annotations</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">\"\"\"</span>\n</pre>\n<p>Install to a specify directory:</p>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">pXXX</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">config</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">annotate</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"\"\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">@requires:</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  [bedtools]</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  validate: \"{{args.bedtools}} --version\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  install: \"conda install -c bioconda bedtools; ln -s $(which bedtools) {{bindir}}/bedtools\"</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">  # other annotations</span>\n<span class=\"s2\">\"\"\"</span>\n</pre>\n<p><code>{{bindir}}</code> will be the directory passed to the command line.</p>\n<pre>pyppl require --pipe &lt;your pipeline&gt; --install &lt;/path/to/bin&gt;\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6386849, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "bcdb45b7eb7960289b1b93abcf1e6bcc", "sha256": "a0c56e33c345934d07487289b45ec558e3ef9b360f905a2c9f03ffec17804817"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pyppl_require-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "bcdb45b7eb7960289b1b93abcf1e6bcc", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 4894, "upload_time": "2019-12-12T19:52:14", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-12-12T19:52:14.811050Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/ed/0f/89007ee641989fd7a6ba4c54d2a4b4ca4e23511d0d93f0a74b35a6d8ea9e/pyppl_require-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "0a941d8314f2c321c975efdbf8daaf22", "sha256": "9f96198cde743ea248bf06776d21efd28d57dc0d260af604eb9ccabc772c8a97"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pyppl_require-0.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "0a941d8314f2c321c975efdbf8daaf22", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 4811, "upload_time": "2019-12-12T19:52:16", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-12-12T19:52:16.984856Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/7a/7a/82089e3ffcfe8d0744c93759f4b6392a1f6c8fe94f4fb27fbc3bf5843d15/pyppl_require-0.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "407ea1042a14e8f950d86cc9350e891e", "sha256": "e8ac05f0b1aa714f90de2b52e78e68f9a4ac85ebdac7312f7a0bd9febf36b1c3"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "pyppl_require-0.0.2-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "407ea1042a14e8f950d86cc9350e891e", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6,<4.0", "size": 4361, "upload_time": "2019-12-28T04:06:03", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-12-28T04:06:03.193087Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/b9/af/b496aacc02a6f273c17cf7bc7cd8454d0ac40b38ac4ba4c81135300e1ca7/pyppl_require-0.0.2-py3